            <title>[SPARK-36464] Fix Underlying Size Variable Initialization in ChunkedByteBufferOutputStream for Writing Over 2GB Data</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-36464</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The `size` method of `ChunkedByteBufferOutputStream` returns a `Long` value; however, the underlying `_size` variable is initialized as `Int`.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That causes an overflow and returns a negative size when over 2GB data is written into `ChunkedByteBufferOutputStream`&lt;/p&gt;</description>
